Devein the prawns, then remove the shells and heads and reserve. Place the shells and heads into a pan with the boiling water and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 5-10 minutes. Strain the liquid through a sieve and reserve the liquor. Discard the heads and shells.In a separate pan, heat the oil over a low heat and add the garlic, cooking gently for 3-4 minutes. Remove the garlic from the oil, turn up the heat and add the prawns. Cook for 1-2 minutes, or until the prawns are beginning to turn pink, then stir in the chopped tomatoes and add the tomato pur√©e.Dissolve the stock cube in the prawn stock and pour into the pan with the prawns. Cook for 3-4 minutes, then stir in the lemon juice, parsley and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Stir in the cooked linguine.Serve the linguine with a drizzle of olive oil.